<paragraph id="8BF0D931B675FFCFFF50B402561CFAC1" blockId="20.[136,1452,1068,2067]" pageId="20" pageNumber="64">
Subshrub 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFF20B402550AFB98" box="[248,359,1068,1095]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="cm" value="27.5" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="15.0">15–40 cm</quantity>
tall, with annual shoots branched off the top of many-headed caudex (taproot) 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFB00B402512EFB98" box="[1240,1347,1068,1095]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="27.5" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="5.0">5–50 mm</quantity>
in diam., or small shrub with annual shoots branched off the second-year shoots terminating caudex. Rounded root 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFAE9B47E51E3FBB4" box="[1329,1422,1104,1131]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 mm</quantity>
in diam. and 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFF23B45A55E8FB50" box="[251,389,1140,1167]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="cm" value="125.0" valueMax="150.0" valueMin="100.0">100–150 cm</quantity>
long covered with fibrously desintegrating dark reddish-brown bark. Lignified shoots unarmed, simple or branched, at base 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFE13B4B65647FB6C" box="[459,554,1176,1203]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
in diam., at the top 1–1,5 mm in diam., with reddish-brown wood covered by yellowish-gray to light brown fibrously disintegrating bark. Annual shoots straight, slender, 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFB46B4925163FB08" box="[1182,1294,1212,1239]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="cm" value="15.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="10.0">10–20 cm</quantity>
long, 0.3–1.0 mm in diam., finely ribbed, glabrous, creamy to yellowish-gray, leafy, with leaf blades gradually narrowed to the top of the shoot. Internodes 7–20(30) mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3558ABAB675FFCFFF65B506565EF7CD" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B675FFCFFF65B50656C2F831" blockId="20.[136,1452,1068,2067]" pageId="20" pageNumber="64">
Generative shoots terminated by thyrses 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFD5AB506568EFA9C" box="[642,739,1320,1347]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="cm" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5–10 cm</quantity>
long with 3–8 well spaced cymes of 2–3 flowers, or by racemes of thyrses. Leaf blades leathery, glabrous, bluish-green, abaxially with prominent reddish midvein and oblique laterals. Bottom leaf blades 15–25(30) × 7–9 (12) mm, oblong to broadly elliptical, almost sessile or at a petiole 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFAF1B55E5106FA54" box="[1321,1387,1392,1419]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long, obtuse, shortly pointed or acuminate at the top, rounded or broadly cuneate at base, flat or slightly revolute and finely undulate at margin, with net of veins, slightly papillate at the base. Upper leaf blades 5–17 × 0.5–2.0 mm, linear-lanceolate to linear-subulate, almost sessile or at a petiole 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFCACB5F25787FA28" box="[884,1002,1500,1527]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
, acute, revolute and finely crenulate at margin, with oblique lateral veins beneath. Ochreas 8–10(12) mm long, lanceolate-tubular, gradually acuminate, at base brownish and papillate, above filmy, transparent, with two light-brown lateral veins, later split in two lateral subulate lacinulas connected with truncate finely incised middle portion. Lateral lacinulas lanceolate, serrate-incised at margins, with a single vein. Ochreolas in thyrses 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFD03B6425757F958" box="[731,826,1644,1671]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7 mm</quantity>
long, oblique funnel-shaped, inflated at base, filmy, at base brownish, above transparent, deeply split in two subulate-lanceolate or subulate-ovate lacinulas at both sides of extremely reduced linear leaf blade, each with light-yellow vein, fimbriate-lacerate or serrate-incised at margin. In flowering perianth is 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFEA0B6F655B9F92C" box="[376,468,1752,1779]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 mm</quantity>
long, with 5 segments green in the middle and white-pinkish at margin, finely crenulate and undulate, with prominent net of veins. Pedicel 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFD12B6D2574AF8C8" box="[714,807,1788,1815]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
long hidden in ochreola and joint to a filiform basal part of tube 0.7–1.0 mm long, which is terminated with cup-shaped or widely funnel-shaped extention 0.7–1.0 mm long and 1.0 mm in diam. Outer segments 2–3 × 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFDA3B76A56B6F880" box="[635,731,1860,1887]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
, rotundate or oblong-ovate, outspread in flowering and fruiting. Inner segments 3.5–4.0 × 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFE6CB7465652F85C" box="[436,575,1896,1923]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="4.35" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.2">4.2–4.5 mm</quantity>
, broadly elliptical, oblong-ovate, or rotundate. Stamens 8, filaments 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFA8CB74651C1F85C" box="[1364,1452,1896,1923]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
long, lanceolate, suddenly broaden at base. Styles 3, 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFD02B7A2570CF878" box="[730,865,1932,1959]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.5 mm</quantity>
long, connated at base to 1/5, with globular stigmas 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B675FFCFFF50B79E5562F814" box="[136,271,1968,1995]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 mm</quantity>
in diam. Fruit trigonous, lanceolate, 3.5–4.5 × 1.8–2.0 mm, sides lanceolate, equal to the inner segments in fruiting, black, finely micro tuberculate, shiny.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B675FFCFFF65B7D6565EF7CD" blockId="20.[136,1452,1068,2067]" box="[189,563,2040,2067]" pageId="20" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B675FFCFFF65B7D65497F7CD" bold="true" box="[189,250,2040,2066]" pageId="20" pageNumber="64">Fl.—</emphasis>
May–June. 
<emphasis id="B93B0523B675FFCFFEA4B7D655D7F7CD" bold="true" box="[380,442,2040,2066]" pageId="20" pageNumber="64">Fr.—</emphasis>
June–Aug.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3558ABAB674FFCEFF65B0B05555FF02" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B674FFCEFF65B0B05555FF02" blockId="21.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFF65B0B05534FF67" bold="true" box="[189,345,158,184]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Distribution:</emphasis>
—Buryatia, along the 
<collectingRegion id="498B17D3B674FFCEFD8EB0B056C2FF67" box="[598,687,158,184]" country="Mongolia" name="Selenge" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Selenga</collectingRegion>
and Chikoy rivers, probably occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="F35899A1B674FFCEFBB4B0B050B4FF67" box="[1132,1241,158,184]" name="Mongolia" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
along the 
<collectingRegion id="498B17D3B674FFCEFA8BB0B051C1FF67" box="[1363,1452,158,184]" country="Mongolia" name="Selenge" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Selenga</collectingRegion>
River (
<figureCitation id="1374C5B4B674FFCEFF0FB0EC554AFF03" box="[215,295,194,220]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[136,229,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1098]" captionTargetId="figure-25@17.[151,1436,190,1098]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Distributional map for Atraphaxis species from Russian Transbaikalia:" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5421130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5421130/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFF0FB0EC554AFF03" bold="true" box="[215,295,194,220]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Fig. 12</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3558ABAB674FFCEFF65B0C850C4FEDF" box="[189,1193,230,256]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B674FFCEFF65B0C850C4FEDF" blockId="21.[136,1452,158,941]" box="[189,1193,230,256]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFF65B0C8554BFEDF" bold="true" box="[189,294,230,256]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Ecology:</emphasis>
—moving dune sands and pine forests along the 
<collectingRegion id="498B17D3B674FFCEFC90B0C857CEFEDF" box="[840,931,230,256]" country="Mongolia" name="Selenge" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Selenga</collectingRegion>
, Chikoy, Khilok rivers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3558ABAB674FFCEFF65B124562BFC73" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B674FFCEFF65B12456D5FEFB" blockId="21.[136,1452,158,941]" box="[189,696,266,292]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFF65B1245553FEFB" bold="true" box="[189,318,266,292]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Etymology</emphasis>
:—Named after the 
<collectingRegion id="498B17D3B674FFCEFDC6B124561AFEFB" box="[542,631,266,292]" country="Mongolia" name="Selenge" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Selenga</collectingRegion>
river.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B674FFCEFF65B100564AFEB3" blockId="21.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFF65B10055A1FE97" bold="true" box="[189,460,302,328]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Chromosome number:</emphasis>
—2n=16, left and right bank of the river Chikoy, 
<quantity id="4CB774D4B674FFCEFC36B1005059FE96" box="[1006,1076,302,329]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" unit="m" value="560.0">560 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFB9AB1005145FE97" author="Ekimova, N. V. &amp; Hrolenko, Yu. A. &amp; Muratova, E. N. &amp; Silkin, P. P." box="[1090,1320,302,329]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" pagination="148 - 153" refId="ref14886" refString="Ekimova, N. V., Hrolenko, Yu. A., Muratova, E. N. &amp; Silkin, P. P. (2009) Chromosome numbers and karyotypes of some species of the family Polygonaceae. Botanicheskii Zhurnal 94 (2): 148 - 153. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="2009">
Ekimova 
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFB77B101508DFE97" box="[1199,1248,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFAEAB10054AFFEB3" author="Chepinoga, V. V." pageId="21" pageNumber="65" refId="ref14814" refString="Chepinoga, V. V. (2014) Chromosome numbers of plant species from Baikal Siberia. Nauka, Novosibirsk, 419 pp." type="book" year="2014">Chepinoga 2014</bibRefCitation>
) sub 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B674FFCEFF26B17D55E2FEB3" box="[254,399,338,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFF26B17D55E2FEB3" box="[254,399,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">A. frutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) K.Koch.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B674FFCEFF65B15850F2FD53" blockId="21.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFF65B1585583FE4F" bold="true" box="[189,494,374,400]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Taxonomic relationships:</emphasis>
—Identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B674FFCEFD7BB1595044FE4F" authority="M. Bieb." authorityName="M. Bieb." box="[675,1065,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Tragopyrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolatum">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFD7BB15957AFFE4F" box="[675,962,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Tragopyrum lanceolatum</emphasis>
M.Bieb.
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFBECB1595163FE4F" box="[1076,1294,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">nom. illeg. superfl.</emphasis>
in herbarium collections (LE, MW) since the 19th century. In “Flora of USSR” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFCB2B1B45794FE6A" author="Pavlov, N. V." box="[874,1017,410,437]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" pagination="501 - 527" refId="ref16510" refString="Pavlov, N. V. (1936) Atraphaxis L. In: Komarov, V. L. (Ed.) Flora URSS, vol. 5. USSR Academy of Sciences, Moscow &amp; Leningrad, pp. 501 - 527. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1936">Pavlov 1936</bibRefCitation>
) and “Floras” of Siberia (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFACDB1B451CAFE6B" author="Krylov, P. N." box="[1301,1447,410,436]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" refId="ref15696" refString="Krylov, P. N. (1930) Flora Siberiae Occidentalis, Ed. sec. et comp. Flora Altaica et provinciae Tomskensis. vol. 4. Salicaceae - Amaranthaceae. Editio sectionis Tomskensis Societatis botanicae Rossicae, Tomsk. 979 pp." type="book" year="1930">Krylov 1930</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFF50B1905558FE07" author="Peshkova, G. A." box="[136,309,446,472]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" refId="ref16672" refString="Peshkova, G. A. (1972) Stepnaya flora Baikalskoy Sibiri [Steppe flora of the Baikal Siberia]. Nauka, Moscow. 207 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1972">Peshkova 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFEE7B19155B6FE07" author="Ivanova, M. M." box="[319,475,446,473]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" pagination="281" refId="ref15129" refString="Ivanova, M. M. (1979) Atraphaxis L. In: Malyshev, L. I. &amp; Peshkova, G. A. (Eds.) Flora of Central Siberia, vol. 1. Nauka, Sib. otdelenie, Novosibirsk. pp. 281. [In Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1979">Ivanova 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFE3EB19056E4FE07" author="Lovelius, O. L." box="[486,649,446,472]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" pagination="114 - 128" refId="ref16068" refString="Lovelius, O. L. (1979) Synopsis generis Atraphaxis L. (Polygonaceae) [A systematic review of the genus Atraphaxis L.] Novitates systematicae plantarum vascularium 1978. Leningrad: Nauka, Vol. 15: 114 - 128. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1979">Lovelius 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFD4CB190575CFE07" author="Kashina, L. I." box="[660,817,446,472]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" pagination="108 - 109" refId="ref15224" refString="Kashina, L. I. (1992) Atraphaxis L. In: Lomonosova, M. N., Bolshakov, N. M. &amp; Krasnoborov, I. M. (Eds.) Flora Sibiriae, vol. 5. Nauka, Sibir. otdel., Novosibirsk, pp. 108 - 109. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1992">Kashina 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFCE4B19057A1FE07" author="Osipov, K. I." box="[828,972,446,472]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" pagination="242 - 254" refId="ref16448" refString="Osipov, K. I. (2001) Polygonaceae. In: Anenkhonov, O. A. (Ed.) Opredelitel rastenyi Buryatii [Key to Buryatia plants]. The Siberian branch of the Russian Acad. Sci. Institute of Experimental and General Biology, Ulan-Ude. pp. 242 - 254. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="2001">Osipov 2001</bibRefCitation>
) is mistaken for 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B674FFCEFB5FB1905116FE07" box="[1159,1403,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFB5FB1905116FE07" box="[1159,1403,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Atraphaxis frutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) K.Koch and reported from Russian Transbaikalia. It resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B674FFCEFC9DB1CD57B8FE23" box="[837,981,482,509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFC9DB1CD57B8FE23" box="[837,981,482,509]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">A. frutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in loose terminal thyrses with well spaced cymes of flowers, but has leafy thyrses, longer ochreas, ochreolas and styles. It differs by the perianth shape and black fruits. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B674FFCEFF0AB20455ABFD9B" box="[210,454,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFF0AB20455ABFD9B" box="[210,454,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Atraphaxis frutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is absent from Russian Transbaikalia but common in East Europe, 
<collectingCountry id="F35899A1B674FFCEFB65B204512EFD9B" box="[1213,1347,554,580]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, Altaisky Kray, the Altai Republic (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFE6BB2605624FDB6" author="Pavlov, N. V." box="[435,585,590,617]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" pagination="501 - 527" refId="ref16510" refString="Pavlov, N. V. (1936) Atraphaxis L. In: Komarov, V. L. (Ed.) Flora URSS, vol. 5. USSR Academy of Sciences, Moscow &amp; Leningrad, pp. 501 - 527. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1936">Pavlov 1936</bibRefCitation>
), Krasnoyarsk Region, Khakassia, Tuva (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFBFEB26050A7FDB7" author="Kashina, L. I." box="[1062,1226,590,616]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" pagination="108 - 109" refId="ref15224" refString="Kashina, L. I. (1992) Atraphaxis L. In: Lomonosova, M. N., Bolshakov, N. M. &amp; Krasnoborov, I. M. (Eds.) Flora Sibiriae, vol. 5. Nauka, Sibir. otdel., Novosibirsk, pp. 108 - 109. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1992">Kashina 1992</bibRefCitation>
), Eastern Mongolia (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFF48B25C5544FD53" author="Grubov, V. I." box="[144,297,626,652]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" refId="ref15062" refString="Grubov, V. I. (1982) Opredelitel sosudistyh rasteniy Mongolii [Key to Mongolia vascular plants, (with atlas)], Nauka, Leningrad, 442 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1982">Grubov 1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFEECB25C55B3FD52" author="Gubanov, I. A." box="[308,478,626,653]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" refId="ref15099" refString="Gubanov, I. A. (1996) Conspectus of Flora of Outer Mongolia: Vascular Plants. Valang, Moscow, 136 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1996">Gubanov 1996</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F35899A1B674FFCEFE29B25C5659FD53" box="[497,564,626,652]" name="China" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFD9AB25C5683FD53" author="Borodina, A. E." box="[578,750,626,652]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" pagination="77 - 129" refId="ref14580" refString="Borodina, A. E. (1989) Polygonaceae. In: Borodina, A. E., Grubov, V. I., Grudzinskaja, I. A. &amp; Menitsky, J. L. (Eds.) Plantae Asiae Centralis, vol. 9. Nauka, Leningrad, pp. 77 - 129. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1989">Borodina 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFD21B25D50FEFD53" author="Bao, B. &amp; Grabovskaya-Borodina, A. E." box="[761,1171,626,653]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" pagination="328 - 332" refId="ref14483" refString="Bao, B. &amp; Grabovskaya-Borodina, A. E. (2003) Atraphaxis L. In: Wu, Z. Y., Raven, P. H. &amp; Hong, D. Y. (Eds.) Flora of China, vol. 5. Science Press, Beijing; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis, pp. 328 - 332. [http: // www. efloras. org / florataxon. aspx? flora _ id = 2 &amp; taxon _ id = 103103]" type="book chapter" year="2003">Bao &amp; Grabovskaya-Borodina 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B674FFCEFF65B2B857DBFC9E" blockId="21.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B674FFCEFF65B2B855ADFD6F" authorityName="O. V. Yurtseva &amp; E. V. Mavrodiev" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,448,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selengensis">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFF65B2B855ADFD6F" box="[189,448,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Atraphaxis selengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B674FFCEFDE6B2B95743FD6F" authority="Kitag." authorityName="Kitag." box="[574,814,662,689]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manshurica">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFDE6B2B9568CFD6F" box="[574,737,662,689]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">A. manshurica</emphasis>
Kitag.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDEA4C0B674FFCEFCE4B2B85041FD6E" author="Nakai, T. &amp; Honda, M. &amp; Satake, Y. &amp; Kitagawa, M." box="[828,1068,662,689]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 78" refId="ref16317" refString="Nakai, T., Honda, M., Satake, Y. &amp; Kitagawa, M. (1936) Index Flora Jeholensis cum Appendice. Planta novae vel minus cognitae ex Manshuria. In: Report of the First Scientific Expedition to Manchoukuo under the Leadership of Shigeyasu Tokunaga June - October 1933. Section IV. Part 4. [Botany], Waseda University, Tokyo. pp. 1 - 78." type="book chapter" year="1936">
Nakai 
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFC50B2B957ACFD6F" box="[904,961,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">et al.</emphasis>
1936: 75
</bibRefCitation>
) from Manchuria (
<collectingCountry id="F35899A1B674FFCEFAD9B2B8512AFD6E" box="[1281,1351,662,689]" name="China" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">China</collectingCountry>
) in leafy thyrses with well spaced cymes of flowers, transparent glossy ochreas and ochreolas, perianth with cup-shaped tube extention and tepals directed to sides in fruiting. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B674FFCEFD7BB2F057C8FD27" authorityName="O. V. Yurtseva &amp; E. V. Mavrodiev" authorityYear="2021" box="[675,933,734,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selengensis">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFD7BB2F057C8FD27" box="[675,933,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Atraphaxis selengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B674FFCEFBEEB2F150B5FD27" box="[1078,1240,734,761]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manshurica">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFBEEB2F150B5FD27" box="[1078,1240,734,761]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">A. manshurica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by broader bottom leaf blades and longer ochreas. Our preliminary study has shown that 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B674FFCEFC6EB32D5035FCC3" authorityName="O. V. Yurtseva &amp; E. V. Mavrodiev" authorityYear="2021" box="[950,1112,770,797]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selengensis">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFC6EB32D5035FCC3" box="[950,1112,770,797]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">A. selengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B674FFCEFB4CB32D5157FCC3" box="[1172,1338,770,797]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manshurica">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFB4CB32D5157FCC3" box="[1172,1338,770,797]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">A. manshurica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share the ITS1–2 region but fall in different subclades in plastid topology (
<figureCitation id="1374C5B4B674FFCEFCBBB30857C8FC9F" box="[867,933,806,832]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[399,1183,207,1891]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[393,1194,187,1925]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. The results of ML and BI analyses applied to the combined chloroplast data set (trnL(UAA) intron + trnL-trnF IGS and rpl32- trnL (UAG) IGS) of Atraphaxis with Bactria ovczinnikovii taken as an outgroup. Numbers above or below branches indicate the aLRT support values equal or more than 0.7 / the posterior probabilities from Bayesian analysis equal or more than 0.9." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5421108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5421108/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFCBBB30857C8FC9F" bold="true" box="[867,933,806,832]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Fig. 1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B674FFCEFF65B364562BFC73" blockId="21.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B674FFCEFF65B36455D3FCBB" authorityName="O. V. Yurtseva &amp; E. V. Mavrodiev" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,446,842,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selengensis">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFF65B36455D3FCBB" box="[189,446,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">Atraphaxis selengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is grouped with 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B674FFCEFDAEB3655695FCBB" authorityName="Jaubert &amp; Spach" authorityYear="1844" box="[630,760,842,869]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="davurica">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B674FFCEFDAEB3655695FCBB" box="[630,760,842,869]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="65">A. davurica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in plastid phylogeny but differs by morphology of the thyrses, leaf blades, and perianth with extremely short filiform low part of perianth tube and a cup-shaped extention, and the outer tepals directed to sides in fruiting.
</paragraph>
